law.text:
The Division Director:
Shall review an application for conversion to a capital stock association;
Shall determine:
Whether the plan is fair to the members of the converting association and the general public;
That insurance of the savings accounts will remain in effect after the conversion;
That, after conversion, the association will be in sound financial condition and will be soundly managed;
That conversion will not impair the capital of the association nor adversely affect the association's operations; and
That no person will receive any inequitable gain or advantage by reason of the conversion; and
May require any changes that are necessary to ensure full disclosure of all material facts.
